        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          Nutty game of football. We started nervously & Liverpool capitalised. Not sure what Walcott was doing trying to run the ball out of the area. He's no good at dribbling into empty space let alone when there are players around. It was some even more comical defending for Liverpool's second although you have to give credit to Firmino. After they went 2-1 up, we probably edged the general play so I think a draw is a fair result. Giroud was very good but all of those who wonder why Arsenal fans get frustrated with him should take a look at his miss from 2 yards away with a simple tap-in into an open goal at his mercy. He misses 10 or so easy chances a season. If he scored them, he'd score 25 league goals minimum and be considered world class, but he doesn't! Campbell's passing has gone up a notch. Not sure whether he always had that in his locker and confidence from playing a run of games has allowed that to come out or it's something he's consciously worked on but either way I'm impressed.

          4 years ago
